Sentencas: Thin film solid oxide fuel cells (TF-SOFCs) having anode-substrate nanostructure that was optimized for the low-temperature operation were fabricated.
Titulo: Nanoporous nickel thin film anode optimization for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Nickel thin film anodes with four different anode thicknesses were deposited on anodic aluminum oxide templates, nanoporous substrates having two different pore sizes, by the sputtering method.
Titulo: Nanoporous nickel thin film anode optimization for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Subse-quently, a yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte and platinum cathode were deposited on them, which completed the entire fuel cell structure.
Titulo: Nanoporous nickel thin film anode optimization for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anode nanostructure of fuel cells in six combinations was analyzed by the cross-sectional view, surface microscopy method, and three-dimensional morphology observation.
Titulo: Nanoporous nickel thin film anode optimization for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Those investigations enabled the anode nanostructure to be identified, such as the anode porosity and the roughness of the interface between anodes and electrolytes.
Titulo: Nanoporous nickel thin film anode optimization for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Then, the six TF-SOFCs were electrochemically characterized in a 500 degrees C operating environment.
Titulo: Nanoporous nickel thin film anode optimization for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power densities were obtained through the i-V-P curves, and the highest performance of 294.1 mW/cm(2) was measured in the cell having a combination of 200 nm-sized porous aluminum anodic oxide (AAO) and 1200 nm-thick Ni anode.
Titulo: Nanoporous nickel thin film anode optimization for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This showed up to 20.1% improvement over the other cells.
Titulo: Nanoporous nickel thin film anode optimization for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: EIS analysis showed that the optimized ohmic and faradaic resistance origi-nated from each part of the unique TF-SOFC structure.
Titulo: Nanoporous nickel thin film anode optimization for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
